<ServiceLayout 
  name="Therapy"
  description="Individual therapy for anxiety, depression, trauma, and life transitions"
>
  <h2>What is Therapy?</h2>
  <p>
    Therapy is a collaborative process where you work with a trained mental health professional to explore your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. Our therapists provide a safe, non-judgmental space to help you navigate life's challenges, develop coping strategies, and work toward meaningful personal growth.
  </p>

  <h2>Who Can Benefit from Therapy?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Individuals experiencing anxiety, depression, or mood difficulties</li>
    <li>Those processing trauma or significant life transitions</li>
    <li>People seeking support with relationship issues or communication skills</li>
    <li>Anyone wanting to better understand themselves and improve their wellbeing</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>
  <p>
    Therapy is tailored to your unique needs and goals. Your therapist will work with you to develop a treatment plan that feels right for you. Sessions typically include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Initial consultation to discuss your concerns and goals</li>
    <li>Regular weekly or bi-weekly sessions (typically 50 minutes)</li>
    <li>Evidence-based therapeutic approaches (CBT, DBT, psychodynamic, etc.)</li>
    <li>Skill-building exercises and homework between sessions</li>
    <li>Ongoing assessment of progress and adjustment of treatment as needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why Choose Us?</h2>
  <p>
    Our therapists are committed to providing <strong>trauma-informed, culturally sensitive care</strong>. We believe in meeting you where you are and working collaboratively toward your goals. Each therapist brings their own expertise and approach, ensuring you can find the right fit for your needs.
  </p>
  <p>
    Whether you're dealing with a specific challenge or seeking general support, our team is here to help you build resilience, develop insight, and create lasting positive change in your life.
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    "Therapy is not about fixing what's broken. It's about discovering what's possible."
  </blockquote>
</ServiceLayout>